  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Addressing the most urgent needs of vulnerable internally displaced persons (IDPs) affected by ramping gang violence in Port-au-Prince, Haiti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) and Protection assistance to vulnerable communities affected by violence. This IOM project provides basic infrastructure services, information systems, and protection assistance, including provision of tailored kits and relocation. The project provides life-saving assistance to 14,000 people, including 4,182 women, 3,826 men, 5,992 children, and 1,000 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
